  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2020-09-18",
    "date": "2020-10-13T15:44:55Z",
    "text": "Safe Indoor Spaces Act\n\nThis bill requires the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) to establish a prize competition to incentivize the development of systems or devices that limit indoor transmission of COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) and the virus that causes it.\n\nTo be eligible for the prize, a system or device must meet certain criteria with respect to decreased viral transmission rates, scalability, and costs.\n\nIn addition, HHS must establish a board comprised of experts in public health, education, small business, and engineering to advise on this competition."
  },
